Anonymous Sun 06 Sep 2020 04:38:31 No.32611316 Report
Quoted By: >>32611518
>>32611098
First, whether or not you have a plot-based story or character-based, the characters matter above all else. They can be lowkey, but knowing your characters sorts out a lot of problems. Plot takes care of itself.
Some writers are the inverse; give them a plot and the characters slot in without being cardboard cutouts.

If you haven't tried a beat sheet or outlining, it can give you some perspective on the puzzle.
My problem was one plot thread that took over was like sticking a silly romcom in the middle of a serious drug/crime novel. I wanted a character downfall, and I sure as hell know the world better now, but a good bit of writing is that "What the hell was I thinking?" feeling.

Try rewriting a section or scene from a slightly different perspective or setting. Sooner or later your instincts will tell you what clicks.
Anonymous
